{{Quote|You know, kid, I think I hired the wrong Carrick. I never had an inside man at a bank before.|Marn Hierogryph, to Zayne Carrick|<ref name="kotor12" />}}
'''Arvan Carrick''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Banker/Legends|banker]] from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Phaeda/Legends|Phaeda]] who lived during the era of the [[Mandalorian Wars]]. [[Marriage/Legends|Married]] to [[Reiva Carrick]] and [[Parent/Legends|father]] of five children, Carrick had one son, [[Zayne Carrick|Zayne]], who was accepted for [[Jedi training/Legends|Jedi training]] at the age of five. While Carrick worked for [[Standard year/Legends|years]] at a [[Bank/Legends|bank]] on Phaeda, Zayne learned the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] ways on the planet [[Taris/Legends|Taris]], until a fateful event in [[3964 BBY]]. Zayne's entire class was [[Padawan Massacre|massacred]] by their [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]], with Zayne the only one to escape. On the run, Zayne was scapegoated for the crime, becoming one of the most wanted men in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].

Never believing that his son was guilty, Carrick was soon transferred to the resort world of [[Telerath/Legends|Telerath]], the corporate crown jewel, a move that Carrick suspected had something to do with Zayne's plight. After only a few [[Standard week/Legends|weeks]], Carrick found himself reunited with his son, who was on Telerath to retrieve a sum of money stored in a frozen account belonging to his "accomplice," [[Snivvian/Legends|Snivvian]] criminal [[Marn Hierogryph]]. Carrick was kidnapped by a pair of [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] known as the [[Moomo Brothers]], whom the Jedi Master [[Raana Tey]] had hired to keep an [[Eye/Legends|eye]] on Zayne's father, although Zayne quickly rescued him from the bumbling hunters' [[Moomo Williwaw|ship]]. Afterward, Carrick helped his son and Hierogryph obtain the money and later moved to work at the [[Jedi Enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] at his son's request.

==Biography==
===Family tragedy===
{{Quote|The transfer came out of the blue. It was a few weeks after we heard about you. All that time, working without notice&mdash;and then just like that! A move to the corporate crown jewel.|Arvan Carrick, to his son, Zayne|<ref name="kotor11" />}}
[[File:Zaynemugshot2-KotORC.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Arvan Carrick's only son, Zayne]]
A [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]]<ref name="kotor11" /> native of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Phaeda/Legends|Phaeda]],<ref name="kotorhb" /> Arvan Carrick worked as a [[Banker/Legends|banker]] in the era of the [[Mandalorian Wars]].<ref name="kotor11" /> At some point, Carrick [[Marriage/Legends|married]] a woman named [[Reiva Carrick|Reiva]], with whom he had five children, including four daughters&mdash;their third child, and only son, [[Zayne Carrick|Zayne]], was [[Reproduction/Legends|born]] in [[3982 BBY]]. The boy showed [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force potential]] from a young age, and [[3977 BBY|just after]] Zayne's fifth [[Birthday/Legends|birthday]], he was brought to the [[Jedi Enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] in the hopes he would be accepted for [[Jedi training/Legends|Jedi training]].<ref name="kotorhb" /> Although [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Vandar Tokare]] confirmed that Zayne only had a marginal proclivity with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], he was impressed with the way the child formed kinships with those around him, and so allowed the boy to be brought into the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]].<ref name="kotor2" /> By [[3964 BBY]], Zayne had become a [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] stationed at the [[Jedi Tower]] of the planet [[Taris/Legends|Taris]], where he trained under Master [[Lucien Draay]].<ref name="kotor1">[[Knights of the Old Republic 1|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 1]]</ref> Carrick, who continued to work at his [[Bank/Legends|bank]] in the meantime,<ref name="kotor8">[[Knights of the Old Republic 8|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 8]]</ref> stayed in touch with his son, visiting him on at least one occasion.<ref name="kotor1" />

That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], Carrick completed his [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] training, and all that was left was to find out whether he would be promoted to the rank of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]]. The five Jedi Masters of the Jedi Tower set up a banquet and a private ceremony for the occasion, and although Carrick and his wife were invited to the meal, they were unable to attend.<ref name="kotor1" /> At the ceremony, four of the five Padawans in the Taris Jedi class were [[Padawan Massacre|murdered]] by their Masters; Zayne, late to the proceedings, was the only one to escape. Zayne became a convenient scapegoat for the massacre and went into hiding as one of the most wanted fugitives in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="kotor2" /> Back home on Phaeda, Carrick and his family never believed that Zayne was responsible. A couple of [[Standard week/Legends|weeks]] after news of the massacre broke, Carrick was suddenly transferred, after years of working at the same bank without notice, to the planet [[Telerath/Legends|Telerath]]. The corporate crown jewel<ref name="kotor11" /> and subject of the [[Telerath Interstellar Banking Initiative]],<ref name="adascorp" /> Telerath was not only a banking world but a resort world as well, where customers stayed in a luxurious setting while meeting one-on-one with representatives. Carrick arrived on Telerath ahead of the rest of his family and began working as a "personal dispute resolution advocate."<ref name="kotor11" />

===Kidnapped===
{{Quote|Somebody's stealing our banker!|Marn Hierogryph|<ref name="kotor12" />}}
[[File:Raana_Moomos_kidnapped_Arvan.png|thumb|right|250px|Arvan Carrick, kidnapped by the Moomo Brothers]]
After only a short [[Time/Legends|time]] on Telerath, Carrick was assigned a very interesting case&mdash;a pair of [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|Arkanian Offshoots]], "[[Jarael|Chantique]]" and "[[Gorman Vandrayk|Baron Margryph]]," were claiming that the [[Baron/Legends|baron's]] account had been frozen due to his name's similarity to that of [[Marn Hierogryph]], a [[Snivvian/Legends|Snivvian]] criminal who was alleged to be Zayne's accomplice. While Carrick tried to resolve their case, he was suddenly set upon by the [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] known as the [[Moomo Brothers]], whom Jedi Master [[Raana Tey]], one of those responsible for the Padawan Massacre, had hired to keep tabs on the man. Directly defying Tey's order to simply watch him, the Moomos kidnapped Carrick. Carrick's new clients gave chase but were unable to catch the Moomos&mdash;however, Carrick was shocked to see his son, Zayne, there too, trying to rescue him from the [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] hunters. Ultimately, the Moomos escaped with Carrick, bringing him to their [[Starship/Legends|ship]], the ''[[Moomo Williwaw]]''.<ref name="kotor11" />

Once on the ship, Carrick was tied up and left in the cargo hold to be watched by [[Del Moomo]]. Meanwhile, Zayne and Marn Hierogryph, who was also on Telerath, hatched a plan to free Carrick. Hierogryph met with [[Dob Moomo]] at a nearby [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] to arrange an exchange: Zayne for his [[Parent/Legends|father]]. As the meeting went on, Zayne sneaked into the ''Moomo Williwaw'' and freed his father from his bonds. By then, a [[Alcohol/Legends|drunken]] Del had stumbled back to the ship to get Carrick. When Hierogryph showed up with a hooded man pretending to be Zayne, Del realized something was afoot and began to argue with his brother&mdash;Zayne hit the brothers with an object using [[Telekinesis/Legends|telekinesis]] and, after the brothers began fighting, took the opportunity to escape with his father. The group all returned to the ship Zayne was using, [[The Last Resort (starship)|''The Last Resort'']], where Carrick learned the whole story. "Chantique" and "Baron Margryph"&mdash;the latter of whom had posed as Zayne during the escape&mdash;were actually named [[Jarael]] and [[Gorman Vandrayk|Camper]] and had been traveling with Zayne and Hierogryph since shortly after the massacre. Still on the run, the group was on Telerath to attempt to withdraw a sum of money that had been in Hierogryph's frozen account. Zayne had no idea that his father was working on Telerath, and it was pure chance that he had been assigned to their case.<ref name="kotor12" />

===Aiding his son===
{{Quote|Even the Jedi Academy on Dantooine has finances to manage. Vandar Tokare is honored by your presence. You and your family are welcome here&mdash;for as long as you like.|Vandar Tokare, to Arvan Carrick|<ref name="kotor12" />}}
[[File:ArvanAndZayne.jpg|thumb|left|205px|Arvan Carrick and his son, Zayne, aboard ''The Last Resort'']]
With the immediate danger behind them, Carrick was able to access the account. At his son's request,<ref name="kotor12" /> Carrick transferred a portion of Zayne's share to [[Shel Jelavan]], a friend of his from Taris whose [[Shay Jelavan|brother]] had been [[Death/Legends|killed]] in the massacre.<ref name="kotor23">[[Knights of the Old Republic 23|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 23]]</ref> After learning that Raana Tey had hired the Moomo Brothers to go after his father, Zayne suggested that Carrick go to Dantooine, where he believed that the family would be safer from attack from the rogue Jedi Masters. Although initially reluctant, Carrick assented to the idea and found himself welcomed with open arms by Master Vandar Tokare. Sympathetic to the Carrick family's situation, Tokare set Carrick to work managing the Jedi Enclave's finances.<ref name="kotor12" /> Carrick continued to work for some time as Tokare's [[Accountant/Legends|accountant]], eventually looking into the [[Draay Trust]]&mdash;the financial trust that held the fortune of the [[Draay family]], which included Zayne's former Master, Lucien Draay&mdash;at Tokare's behest. Carrick found a great deal of previously unknown wealth in the trust, which Tokare suspected could have been used to create Jedi shadow agents loyal only to the Draays.<ref name="kotor31">[[Knights of the Old Republic 31|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 31]]</ref>

Zayne was eventually able to clear his name and opted to pass up an opportunity to return to the Jedi Order in favor of going into [[Cargryph Capital Management|business]] with his friend, Marn Hierogryph. Carrick's son also had another project in mind&mdash;an idea he dubbed the [[Rogue Moon Project]], an organization meant to aid [[Refugee/Legends|refugees]], wrongly accused fugitives, and other individuals without hope. To this end, Carrick helped manage his son's finances, investing money that Zayne brought in from a con on the [[Metellos Exchange]] auction house and from a bounty collected on the head of the "[[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] Strangler," [[Toki Tollivar]]. This money funded a [[Rogue Moon Project Command|headquarters]] for the Rogue Moon Project, hidden in a warehouse on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="kotor48">[[Knights of the Old Republic 48|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 48]]</ref>

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|We never asked. We know you. You didn't do it.''"<br />"''Dad&hellip;''"<br />"''And if you did&hellip; well, it was probably something you had to do.|Arvan Carrick and his son, Zayne, regarding Zayne's alleged crimes|<ref name="kotor12" />}}
In the aftermath of his son's alleged crimes on Taris, Arvan Carrick and the rest of his family refused to believe that Zayne was responsible and, furthermore, if he was responsible, figured that he had been forced to do that of which he was accused. Although Carrick was deeply affected by his son's predicament,<ref name="kotor12" /> he hid it as well as he could while working on Telerath.<ref name="kotor11" /> His transfer to Telerath came as a big surprise to Carrick&mdash;he figured that it had to have something to do with his son, not believing that he had been noticed on his own merit.<ref name="kotor12" /> As a representative, Carrick was very polite to his clients and tolerated "Baron Margryph's" repeated furious outbursts. Carrick was helpless against the Moomo Brothers and was easy prey to be kidnapped. While being ushered to the ''Moomo Williwaw'', Carrick was absolutely stunned to see his son, Zayne,<ref name="kotor11" /> who later rescued him. Carrick was initially reluctant to move to Dantooine as Zayne suggested but agreed anyway, trusting that his son's idea was prudent for the safety of the family. Carrick had light skin with [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and [[Eye/Legends|eyes]], wearing a mustache during his time on Telerath.<ref name="kotor12" />

==Behind the scenes==
Arvan Carrick first appeared in ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic: Reunion]]'', the third story arc of the [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic (comic series)|''Knights of the Old Republic'']] [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] series, written by [[John Jackson Miller]] and released from [[December]] [[2006]] to [[January]] [[2007]].<ref name="kotor11" /><ref name="kotor12" /> Carrick had been mentioned in previous installments of the series as the father of protagonist Zayne Carrick,<ref name="kotor1" /><ref name="kotor2" /> but he was not identified as Arvan Carrick until ''Reunion''. In the two issues of ''Reunion'', Carrick was drawn by two different artists, [[Brian Ching]]<ref name="kotor11" /> and [[Harvey Tolibao]].<ref name="kotor12" /> Carrick went on to be mentioned in several later ''Knights of the Old Republic'' issues.<ref name="kotor31" /><ref name="kotor48" />

